<subSubSection lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="140" pageId="10" pageNumber="139" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="10.[136,1452,1228,2083]" pageId="10" pageNumber="139">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,481,1552,1579]" pageId="10" pageNumber="139">Distribution and habitat</emphasis>
:―This subspecies is endemic to Milos island group and has been located so far on the following islands and islets: Milos, Kimolos, Prasonisi, Poliegos, at elevations from sea level to ca. 87 meters. It has been found in a number of different habitats such as sandy shores, rocky and gravelly places next to the sea, phrygana formations, maquis and periodically flooded areas, all on acid volcanic substrates.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[136,1452,1228,2083]" pageId="10" pageNumber="139">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,256,1697,1723]" pageId="10" pageNumber="139">Notes</emphasis>
:―Although the pink-coloured ligules is a remarkable trait observed in this subspecies, it is not characteristic of all the known populations. Ligules in various shades of pink, from deep- to pale-pink, or white tinged pink, or totally white have been recorded, even among individuals from the same locality. The morphological features that separate 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Biel &amp; Kit Tan" authorityYear="2020" box="[136,523,1804,1830]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Anthemis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="10" pageNumber="139" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="rigida" subSpecies="runemarkii">
<emphasis box="[136,315,1804,1830]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="139">Anthemis rigida</emphasis>
subsp. 
<emphasis box="[399,523,1804,1830]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="139">runemarkii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the rest of the ligulate subspecies are mainly the narrow leaf lobes, the longer and wider involucre and the broad scarious margin of the outer involucral bracts (
<figureCitation box="[1074,1144,1840,1867]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="9.[136,229,1943,1965]" captionTargetBox="[152,1435,191,1917]" captionTargetId="figure-17@9.[151,1436,190,1918]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 5. Photographs of Anthemis rigida in the field (a, c, e, g) and in cultivation (b, d, f, h): A. rigida subsp. rigida from Kriti (a &amp; b); A. rigida subsp. liguliflora from Kithira (c &amp; d); A. rigida subsp. runemarkii from Milos (e &amp; f); A. rigida subsp. antri-neptuni from Karpathos (g &amp; h) (all photos taken by the first author except c, by Stavroula Fatsea)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5421348" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5421348/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="139">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
, 
<tableCitation box="[1157,1244,1840,1867]" captionStart="TABLE 5" captionStartId="7.[136,224,1534,1558]" captionText="TABLE 5. Comparison of morphological features among the five subspecies of Anthemis rigida in the Aegean. Uncommon character values are in parentheses. All measurements in mm." pageId="10" pageNumber="139">Table 5</tableCitation>
). The “adpressedpubescent” achenes that Biel &amp; Kit Tan (2020) mention in their description raises serious questions about achene morphology for the entire genus: the only report of hairy achenes among the 
<taxonomicName box="[1007,1200,1912,1938]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Anthemis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="10" pageNumber="139" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[1007,1111,1912,1938]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="139">Anthemis</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
of Europe (
<bibRefCitation author="Fernandes, R." pageId="10" pageNumber="139" pagination="145 - 159" refId="ref7207" refString="Fernandes, R. (1976) Anthemis L. In: Tutin, T. G., Heywood, V. H., Burges, N. A., Moore, D. M., Valentine, D. H., Walters, S. M. &amp; Webb, D. A. (Eds.) Flora Europaea 4. Cambridge University Press, Cambridge, pp. 145 - 159." type="book chapter" year="1976">Fernandes 1976</bibRefCitation>
), 
<collectingCountry box="[214,294,1948,1974]" name="Turkey" pageId="10" pageNumber="139">Turkey</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Grierson, A. J. C. &amp; Yavin, Z." box="[307,570,1948,1975]" pageId="10" pageNumber="139" pagination="174 - 221" refId="ref7540" refString="Grierson, A. J. C. &amp; Yavin, Z. (1975) Anthemis L. In: Davis, P. H. (Ed.) Flora of Turkey and the East Aegean islands. Edinburgh University Press, Edinburgh, pp. 174 - 221." type="book chapter" year="1975">Grierson &amp; Yavin 1975</bibRefCitation>
), N Africa (
<bibRefCitation author="Oberprieler, C." box="[698,894,1948,1975]" pageId="10" pageNumber="139" pagination="5 - 328" refId="ref7787" refString="Oberprieler, C. (1998) The systematics of Anthemis L. (Compositae, Anthemideae) in W and C North Africa. Bocconea 9: 5 - 328." type="journal article" year="1998">Oberprieler 1998</bibRefCitation>
), Middle East (
<bibRefCitation author="Eig, A." box="[1062,1167,1948,1975]" pageId="10" pageNumber="139" pagination="161 - 224" refId="ref7179" refString="Eig, A. (1938) Taxonomic studies on the oriental species of the genus Anthemis. Palestine Journal of Botany 1: 161 - 224." type="journal article" year="1938">Eig 1938</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Iranshahr, M." box="[1178,1348,1948,1974]" pageId="10" pageNumber="139" pagination="5 - 44" refId="ref7615" refString="Iranshahr, M. (1986) Anthemis. In: Rechinger, K. H. (Ed.) Flora Iranica 158, Compositae: VI Anthemideae. Akademische Druck und Verlagsanstalt, Graz, pp. 5 - 44." type="book chapter" year="1986">Iranshahr 1986</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Ghafoor, A. &amp; Ali, S. J." pageId="10" pageNumber="139" pagination="1 - 41" refId="ref7458" refString="Ghafoor, A. &amp; Ali, S. J. (2002) The genus Anthemis L. (Compositae) in Iraq: a synopsis. Compositae Newsletter 38: 1 - 41." type="journal article" year="2002">Ghafoor &amp; Ali 2002</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<collectingCountry box="[323,467,1984,2010]" name="Saudi Arabia" pageId="10" pageNumber="139">Saudi Arabia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Ghafoor, A." box="[481,641,1984,2011]" pageId="10" pageNumber="139" pagination="79 - 98" refId="ref7425" refString="Ghafoor, A. (2010) The genus Anthemis L. (Compositae-Anthemideae) in Arabian Peninsula: a taxonomic study. Pakistan Journal of Botany 42: 79 - 98." type="journal article" year="2010">Ghafoor 2010</bibRefCitation>
) concerns “a single poor specimen with somewhat hairy young achenes” that 
<bibRefCitation author="Eig, A." box="[187,310,2020,2047]" pageId="10" pageNumber="139" pagination="161 - 224" refId="ref7179" refString="Eig, A. (1938) Taxonomic studies on the oriental species of the genus Anthemis. Palestine Journal of Botany 1: 161 - 224." type="journal article" year="1938">Eig (1938)</bibRefCitation>
mentions from Ramadi, 
<collectingCountry box="[599,648,2021,2047]" name="Iraq" pageId="10" pageNumber="139">Iraq</collectingCountry>
. A thorough examination of achenes in all the specimens collected on Milos do not indicate the presence of any pubescence.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[136,1451,158,257]" pageId="11" pageNumber="140">
As previously mentioned, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Biel &amp; Kit Tan" authorityYear="2020" box="[488,879,158,184]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Anthemis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="11" pageNumber="140" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="rigida" subSpecies="runemarkii">
<emphasis box="[488,668,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="140">Anthemis rigida</emphasis>
subsp. 
<emphasis box="[755,879,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="140">runemarkii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
co-exist with 
<taxonomicName authority="subsp. rigida" box="[1042,1298,158,185]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Anthemis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="11" pageNumber="140" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="rigida" subSpecies="rigida">
<emphasis box="[1042,1142,158,185]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="140">A. rigida</emphasis>
subsp. 
<emphasis box="[1230,1298,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="140">rigida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on the island of Milos. In the areas where the two taxa meet, subpopulations with intermediate features have been recorded. Similar cases are reported by 
<bibRefCitation author="Greuter, W. &amp; Rechinger, K. H." box="[379,697,230,257]" pageId="11" pageNumber="140" pagination="22 - 196" refId="ref7516" refString="Greuter, W. &amp; Rechinger, K. H. (1967) Chloris Kythereia. Boissiera 13: 22 - 196." type="journal article" year="1967">Greuter &amp; Rechinger (1967)</bibRefCitation>
for populations on Kithira and Antikithira islands.
</paragraph>
